==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ruddock
<hw>Rud"dock</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>ruddic</ets>; cf. W. <ets>rhuddog</ets> the redbreast. ⟦root⟧113.
See <er>Rud</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>raddock</asp>.]</altsp> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The
European robin.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The tame <xex>ruddock</xex> and the coward
kite.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A piece of gold money; -- probably because the gold
of coins was often reddened by copper alloy. Called also <altname>red
ruddock</altname>, and <altname>golden ruddock</altname>.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Great pieces of gold . . . red <qex>ruddocks</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Florio.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ruddy</ent>⟦br⟧
